text.tspan: Bookx Reader
Bookx Reader can be open by directly selecting the book from Files or by Double Clicking the book in Library view.
This view isn't going to create a new window but should be in the same window. Opening another instance would then again present the Library view.
Back button here, thereby is to go back to library view and restore the window size to saved library window size.
The Reader by default opens in Maximum window size.
There usually is going to be a brief period of book loading, which should be presented with a spinner.
- Work on Table of contents, Bookmark and Highlight section.
On mouse hover over on top headerbar should reveal it's primary buttons, otherwise headerbar
merges with the book content in style with only Book Name visible in Header title after a certain period
of time (like 3-5 sec).
The same happens with the bottom book navigation panel buttons, visible only when mouse hover the
bottom area.
Right/Left Navigation is done by clicking right/left most area in the content.

Layout
The bottom panel switches to non-focus, and shows current page on the left and chapter name and
time to finish on the right.
We should also enable pinch-to-zoom gesture for the content.
The popover appears on selecting a text, or clicking a highlighted text.
The popover contains:
- Highlight button
- Comment button
- Translate button
- Search on Wikipedia
- Copy to Clipboard
- Delete comment/highlight (activated when text has comment or is highlighted)
Right after clicking highlight button, the default highlight (yellow) is applied (using <mark>
tag), and array of selectable color options appear from right.
Selecting the comment button activate a text box to write text, clicking aywhere in the
content the text box disappears, leaving a yellow underline on the text. It reappears on
clickning the commented text.
